column4: " Usually played either in C or Eb - I have modulated fairly freely between these (and Gb) in the introduction before playing in tempo and staying in Eb. The First 8 Bars are often thought of as 'slash' chords - a series of triads over
"Last 16 bars of the song played freely"
"Black note glissando with sus pedal down on GbMaj7/Eb"
"Becomes G phrygian (i.e. an Eb scale is used over a G bass note)"
"Diatonic chords from Eb Major over G Bass (i.e. G phrygian) - note no accidentals."
"Trio starts - I tried to play in the style of Chick Corea/Keith Jarrett trios with lots of space"
"On bars 1-7 and bars 17-21 I mainly thought of triads with neighbour tones."
"Gb/Eb - triad arpeggio with some neighbour tones"
"Eb - simple triad with neighbour/or passing tones."
"Anticipates key change to Gb coming in next bar"
"Up Gb Scale in rhythm based on 16th triplets."
"One note repeated in some sort of rhythm"
"More little melodic figures based on triads (Eb)"
"Scale fragment played in thirds - over Am7b5 D7alt"
"On Eb a little repeating figure on 5th and lower neighbour is developed with another tone above that changes as the chords change"
"G is lowered to Gb in figure"
"A new melodic figure also based on triads"
"Figure is developed with notes changed to fit the new triads as trhey arrive"
"On Dm7b5 fast Eb scale up to G as target tone arriving right on beat 3 for the G7 chord"
